only\n4. Update ONLY these cells (rows 2, 3, 4 — columns B, C, D):\n\nRow 2 (Opportunity 1):\n  B2 = \"Renegotiate Salesforce Enterprise Contract\"\n  C2 = \"• Salesforce at $3.1M is 40% of total portfolio spend.\\n• Audit active seats; renegotiate multi-year terms; bundle Slack billing.\\n• 10–15% savings target reduces single-vendor concentration risk.\"\n  D2 = 389653  (type: 'n' — numeric)\n\nRow 3 (Opportunity 2):\n  B3 = \"Exit Long-tail Vendor Portfolio\"\n  C3 = \"• 344 vendors under $50K total $1.55M with minimal strategic value.\\n• Issue termination notices; redirect spend to preferred panel vendors.\\n• 10–20% realised after notice periods and minimum commitments.\"\n  D3 = 232893  (type: 'n' — numeric)\n\nRow 4 (Opportunity 3):\n  B4 = \"Consolidate Global Office Footprint\"\n  C4 = \"• Eight flexible office vendors total $956K with significant overlap.\\n• Exit GPT, WeWork, Work Easy; retain TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower.\\n• 15–20% cost reduction through lease exits and anchor renegotiations.\"\n  D4 = 167239  (type: 'n' — numeric)\n\nIMPORTANT constraints:\n- Do NOT touch A1, A2, A3, A4 or any other cells\n- Do NOT use aoa_to_sheet or sheet_to_json or json_to_sheet to rebuild the sheet\n- Use encode_cell like this example:\n    ws[XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r:1, c:1})] = { t:'s', v: \"some text\" };\n    ws[XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r:1, c:3})] = { t:'n', v: 389653 };\n- Row index is 0-based: row 2 = r:1, row 3 = r:2, row 4 = r:3\n- Column index: A=0, B=1, C=2, D=3\n- After writing all cells, save with XLSX.writeFile\n- The xlsx module is at: C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/node_modules/xlsx\n\nWrite the script, run it, and confirm it completed without errors.\n\nThen read back the saved file and print cells B2, C2, D2, B3, C3, D3, B4, C4, D4 to verify the data was written correctly.","agentId":"aafa9741835ae9229","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 9 cells verified correctly. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n**Script written:** `C:/Users/rjega/